IS YOUR APP CUSTOMER-READY? -- PRE-LAUNCH CHECKLIST
LaunchLook · 30-45 minutes
{% if customer and customer.app_name %}Prepared for {{ customer.app_name }}{% if customer.tier %} (bundled with {{ customer.tier }}){% endif %}{% endif %}

Work through this in order on your live site (not your editor preview).
If you fail an item, fix it before moving on.

LaunchLook checks many of these automatically as part of your audit --
your job is to confirm each one is actually true on the live site.

Total time: 30-45 minutes, plus the "watch someone use it" step at the end.

---

1. FIRST LOOK (~5 min -- homepage and footer)
[ ] Live link loads quickly, no spinning.
[ ] Padlock in URL bar (no "Not Secure" warning).
[ ] Browser tab shows your app name and a real favicon -- not a generic globe or builder default.
[ ] A stranger can tell what the app does within a few seconds from the homepage alone.
[ ] No placeholder text (lorem ipsum, "Your Company Name," TODO notes).
[ ] No default "welcome to your new app" builder copy.
[ ] Your product name in the header, not the platform's logo.
[ ] Nothing "developer only" visible (test buttons, skip-login, seed data).
[ ] Main homepage button does what it promises.

2. DATA HYGIENE (~3 min -- the most common pre-launch miss)
[ ] Test accounts, fake users, and seed data deleted (or clearly labelled "Demo").
[ ] No real names, emails, or photos from beta testers visible to new visitors.
[ ] Your own admin/dev account isn't showing up in any public list.
[ ] Any "example" content reads like real content a customer would expect to see.

3. TRUST & CONTACT (~3 min)
[ ] /privacy page exists and describes what data you actually collect (not a blank template).
[ ] /terms page exists and reflects your actual terms (not a blank template).
[ ] Visitors can find how to reach you.
[ ] That email is real and monitored -- not support@example.com.
[ ] Footer privacy/terms links work (no 404).

4. DOES THE MAIN FLOW WORK? (~10 min)
[ ] Buttons and links do something -- no dead ends.
[ ] Signup confirmation email arrives within a minute (check spam too).
[ ] Email from your app lands in the inbox, not spam.
[ ] You can log in after signing up.
[ ] You can log out.
[ ] Contact and signup forms aren't getting flooded by spam submissions.
[ ] Core workflow completes end-to-end (book, pay, submit, save).
[ ] Form submission shows a clear success or failure message.
[ ] Test payment completes with a sensible thank-you page.
[ ] New user isn't staring at a blank screen with no guidance.

5. WHEN THINGS GO WRONG (~5 min)
[ ] Wrong password shows a clear message, not a crash or generic error.
[ ] A made-up URL (yoursite.com/asdf) shows a 404 page with a link back home.
[ ] Refreshing mid-workflow doesn't wipe the user's progress without warning.
[ ] Closing the tab and coming back: signed-in state behaves sensibly.

6. ON A PHONE (~5 min)
[ ] No sideways scrolling.
[ ] Text readable without pinching to zoom.
[ ] Buttons easy to tap, not tiny.
[ ] Main workflow usable on phone, not only desktop.
[ ] Email field shows the @ key, number fields show the number pad.

7. SHARING YOUR LINK (~2 min)
[ ] Paste URL into Slack, iMessage, or LinkedIn -- preview shows the right title, description, and image, not builder default.

8. IF YOUR APP HAS USER ACCOUNTS (required if applicable -- skip only if your app has no accounts at all)
[ ] Signed in as person A, you cannot see person B's private data.
[ ] When signed out, protected pages ask you to log in instead of showing someone else's data.
[ ] Password reset flow works end-to-end: request email, receive it, set new password, log in successfully.

9. THE REAL TEST (~10-15 min -- highest-value step on this list -- don't skip it)
[ ] You've watched one person who isn't you try to use the app, without coaching them.
[ ] They got through the main workflow without asking for help.
[ ] You'd be comfortable sending this link to a friend today.
[ ] You wouldn't be embarrassed if someone screenshotted the homepage.

---

WHAT TO DO NEXT
- Fix before you share widely: broken signup, missing privacy/terms, placeholder text,
  dev-only buttons visible, seed data exposed, one user seeing another's data.
- Fix soon after launch: mobile layout quirks, weak link previews, empty screens
  without guidance, error messages that crash instead of explain.
- More than ~5 serious problems? Pause the launch push until the worst ones are handled.

